                <block>
                    <h2>Chalk</h2>
                    <image src="p044a.png" title=""/>
                </block>
                <p>Chalk is a type of <sSpan class="mm_inlineNumber mm_halfSpace">1</sSpan><dropDown id="dropDown_1" example="y">
                        <item id="item_1">plastic</item>
                        <item id="item_2" correct="y">rock</item>
                    </dropDown> that is <sSpan class="mm_inlineNumber mm_halfSpace">2</sSpan><dropDown id="dropDown_2">
                        <item id="item_1" correct="y">made</item>
                        <item id="item_2">washed</item>
                    </dropDown> under the ocean. This is too hard to draw with, so it’s made into chalk sticks for artists.</p>
                <p>The chalk rock is <sSpan class="mm_inlineNumber mm_halfSpace">3</sSpan><dropDown id="dropDown_3">
                        <item id="item_1" correct="y">ground</item>
                        <item id="item_2">picked</item>
                    </dropDown> into a powder. The chalk powder is <sSpan class="mm_inlineNumber mm_halfSpace">4</sSpan><dropDown id="dropDown_4">
                        <item id="item_1">roasted</item>
                        <item id="item_2" correct="y">mixed</item>
                    </dropDown> with water and a color pigment to make a <sSpan class="mm_inlineNumber mm_halfSpace">5</sSpan><dropDown id="dropDown_5">
                        <item id="item_1" correct="y">paste</item>
                        <item id="item_2">pencil</item>
                    </dropDown>. Then the paste is made into thin stick shapes and <br/><sSpan class="mm_inlineNumber mm_halfSpace">6</sSpan><dropDown id="dropDown_6">
                        <item id="item_1" correct="y">dried</item>
                        <item id="item_2">cooled</item>
                    </dropDown> in an oven.</p>
                <p>Oil is sometimes added to artists’ chalk to make it softer. And more pigment is added, so the color is darker than chalk that’s used for writing on <sSpan class="mm_inlineNumber mm_halfSpace">7</sSpan><dropDown id="dropDown_7">
                        <item id="item_1">paper</item>
                        <item id="item_2" correct="y">blackboards</item>
                    </dropDown>.</p>
            </block>
        </block>
    </main>
